; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; calc_iscv: idle speed control - compute ISC valve duty target
;
; Called from the main 4ms loop (divide_d_by_x, guarded by "tbs bit1,unk_44"
; at loc_D380 - purpose of that gate not yet confirmed). Produces
; var_iscv_target_rpm/var_iscv_rpm_cmp_197 (target idle RPM and RPM error)
; in its first chunk, then a duty value in var_iscv_19D in its second chunk.
;
; Downstream (back in divide_d_by_x, loc_D44B): var_iscv_19D is combined with
; battery dead-time compensation (calc_idle_batt1/calc_idle_batt2) and written
; to var_iscv_pwm, which drive_dout1_iscv turns into an actual CPR1/DOUT.1
; timed pulse to the ISC valve solenoid every 4ms.
;
; Full write-up: docs/idle_control_system.md
;
; SECTION 1 (D4E4..D602): Flare/enrichment terms and target RPM
;   - var_iscv_startup_flare: decays -1/tick after startup, or set from
;     max(ECT,THA)/16 once startup window (0x3D ticks) has passed
;   - var_iscv_pim_flare: PIM-indexed extra air on throttle lift-off
;     (var_flags_4E.4), decays -8/tick otherwise
;   - unk_1A9: fixed 0x300 during startup window, then decays -4/tick
;   - unk_1AB: 0x200 during the first 15 ticks if CPU2 cold-enrichment
;     (dmarx_idle_enrich) is active, else 0 once var_cnt_EA elapses
;   - unk_1AD: ramps +/-2/tick toward a load-dependent set-point selected
;     from byte_C36C/C372/C374 via var_flags_4F bits 1/2/3/4 (hypothesis:
;     these consolidate raw A/C (var_diag_errors_5.5) and PS/IDUP
;     (var_io_input2.3) switch state for idle-up compensation - not confirmed)
;   - byte_C36C/C36E/C370 threshold check sets var_diag_errors_5.0 and feeds
;     check_knock_sensor_err_flag + unk_1A7 (exact meaning of this
;     diagnostic-linked term not confirmed)
;   - var_iscv_target_rpm = unk_1AD + unk_1A9 + unk_1AB + table_iscv_C391
;     entry (selected by var_io_input2 bits 6/7 - load switches, meaning
;     of the individual bits not confirmed)
;   - var_iscv_rpm_cmp_197 = (var_rpm_x_5p12 - var_iscv_target_rpm) / 16,
;     saturated - i.e. the idle RPM error
;
; SECTION 2 (D612..D67F): var_iscv_target_base update
;   - At idle with var_cnt_DB elapsed: look up var_iscv_rpm_cmp_197 in
;     table_iscv_rpm_C357 (linear search, ascending bands) and derive a
;     candidate baseline from the matched entry + var_iscv_target_base
;   - Otherwise: candidate baseline is var_nv_idle_trim (or 0x66 default)
;     scaled by 16
;   - Candidate is clamped against nv_idle_trim-relative limits and the
;     larger of (candidate, previous var_iscv_target_base) is kept -
;     var_iscv_target_base only ratchets, never drops, except when clamped
;
; SECTION 3 (D67F..D6C9): ECT/PIM-based unk_1A0 and unk_1A1 duty terms
;   - unk_1A0: ECT-indexed (byte_C352/C354, table_ect_fixed4_interpolate)
;     correction, combined with unk_1A7 via interp_y_pair
;   - unk_1A1: second RPM-band lookup (table_iscv_rpm_C361, same search
;     pattern as table_iscv_rpm_C357) when idle detected, else falls back
;     to a fixed default; result is clamped to +/-0x400 of unk_1A1's
;     previous value (rate-of-change limit)
;
; SECTION 4 (D6C9..D815): Idle trim (var_nv_idle_trim) learning
;   - Mirrors the AFR trim learning pattern (see nv_afr_trim_base in
;     calc_4ms_corrections): when idle has been stable long enough
;     (var_cnt_DD/var_cnt_DE counters), var_idle_trim is nudged via
;     idle_trim_limits and written back to NV RAM (var_nv_idle_trim) via
;     write_rB_nv_ram, so the ISCV baseline adapts over time
;   - unk_9E appears to gate/flag the direction or validity of a pending
;     trim nudge (not fully confirmed)
;
; SECTION 5 (D815..D863): unk_1A3/unk_1A5 RPM-slope-based terms
;   - unk_1A5: signed quarter-rate-limited tracking of var_rpm_x_5p12
;   - unk_1A3: doubled/saturated derivative-like term from the above,
;     clamped to 0x400 under most conditions
;
; SECTION 6 (D863..D92D): Final 2D map lookup -> var_iscv_19D
;   - table_idle_C2FE via map_rD_rX_interpolate (bilinear): the main
;     RPM-error/load idle map
;   - var_iscv_unk_19F: intermediate clamped to max 0x50 (80)
;   - ECT-based gating (var_cnt_DC, RPM 2800/3000 bands) selects between
;     the map result and an RPM-table (table_rpm_c31d) fallback, also
;     toggling var_flags_4E.3 and var_flags_4F.6
;   - Final result stored to var_iscv_19D (consumed by divide_d_by_x as
;     described above)
;
; NOTE: several intermediate terms (unk_1A0/1A1/1A3/1A5/1A7/1A9/1AB/1AD,
; unk_9E, unk_E2) are understood at the level of "a flare/ramp/compensation
; contribution combined additively into the target" but not fully
; distinguished from one another - left unrenamed rather than guessed at.
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

