; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; calc_4ms_corrections: main 4ms ignition and fuel correction calculations
;
; Called from the 4ms main loop (via divide_d_by_x chunk dispatch).
; Computes all the per-cycle correction factors used by the ignition and
; injection scheduling code.
;
; SECTION 1 (EA22..EA95): Dwell parameters and mode flag initialisation
;   - Ignition limp mode: if var_cnt_C7 < 61 ticks (244ms post-start)
;   - var_ign_dwell_offset: battery * RPM factor (coil inductance compensation)
;   - var_ign_dwell_min: minimum dwell from RPM table
;   - var_flags_4E mode flag update from var_flags_4E_saved
;   - Overrun advance: RPM/gear/IDL table lookup -> var_overrun_advance
;
; SECTION 2 (EAAC..EB54): Closed loop and idle mode detection
;   - Closed loop enable (var_flags_4E.1): requires startup time 368ms,
;     RPM > 1000, speed > 3 kph, ECT > 70C, battery > 8.6V
;   - IDL signal: clears closed-loop and idle flags when throttle opens
;   - Idle detect (var_flags_4E.2): gear ratio, RPM slope, closed-loop
;   - Idle timing ramp reset: sets var_idle_timing_ramp = 0xFF when opening
;   - Overrun detect (var_flags_4E.3): IDL + RPM slope + gearing conditions
;
; SECTION 3 (EC24..EC33): Snapshot and gate check
;   - Save var_flags_4E -> var_flags_4E_copy_1D3 (used by update_idle_timing_ramp)
;   - Run knock_retard_decay
;   - If var_schedule_flag_41.1 set: injection already done, skip to return
;
; SECTION 4 (EC33..EC93): Open-loop ignition correction (var_open_loop_ign_corr)
;   - Integrates towards 0x80 (centre) when not at idle or below ECT threshold
;   - At idle + low PIM + no sensor error: interpolate from ECT/PIM tables
;   - Result stored in var_open_loop_ign_corr
;
; SECTION 5 (EC93..EC24 continued): Lambda and injection flags
;   - var_flags_4E bit management (closed loop, overrun, fuel cut)
;   - Injection mode determination
;
; SECTION 6 (ED23..EDCB): Per-cylinder RPM deviation and ignition advance trim
;   - Tracks per-cylinder ne_sum3 into var_cyl_rpm_dev[4]
;   - Computes var_ign_advance_trim from cylinder-to-cylinder RPM spread
;
; SECTION 7 (EE1D..EEBD): Fuel trim, knock retard and advance max ramp
;   - Assembles dmatx_knock_retard from lambda, knock and combined corrections
;   - Ramps var_ign_advance_max based on RPM stability
;
; SECTION 8 (EF48..EFB0): Final knock base and cold advance
;   - Computes var_ign_knock_retard_base from corrections
;   - Calls calc_ign_timing_min
;   - Sets var_ign_cold_advance for ignition scheduling
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

