;           var_ne_sum3 = time for 45 crank degrees in 4us units
;           var_ign_ne_frac = sub-NE fractional period for interpolation
;
; Formula:
;   main = A * var_ne_sum3 / 6        integer part of timer offset
;   frac = B * var_ign_ne_frac / 256  sub-degree fractional correction
;   result = main + frac              total CPR offset in 4us units
;
; The /6 relates to: ne_sum3 covers 45 degrees, and timing is stored
; in units where 6 counts = 45/7.5 degrees, so A/6 * ne_sum3 = timer_units.
; Returns result in X (and D).
